# Focus-Fork: Async Inbox Client

This is a **focus-first, email-like fork** of TelegramSwift. All behavioral changes are **always on** — there is no user toggle.

## Core invariant

```swift
FocusProduct.isEnabled // always true in this fork
```

**We do not care about preserving the stock (non-focus) Telegram behavior.** Code can be modified directly without `FocusProduct.isEnabled` guards when the change only makes sense for the focus fork. The flag still exists for greppability but wrapping every change in a conditional is not required.

## Design pillars

- **Async over live**: no typing indicators, no online presence, no read receipts in the list
- **Mail-like**: full-width messages, no chat bubbles, author name as header, generous vertical spacing
- **Inbox not chat**: chat list shows "Pinned" / "Inbox" section headers; channels are hidden and surfaced via a Digest banner
- **Minimal chrome**: no avatars in list rows, no story rings, no emoji/keyboard/gift buttons in composer, no send/read ticks on list rows
- **Subdued light theme**: light palette locked; no dark mode, no auto-night switching

## Key customisation files

| Concern | File |
|---|---|
| List sections + digest injection | `ChatListController.swift` |
| List row appearance | `ChatListRowItem.swift`, `ChatListRowView.swift` |
| Section header row | `ChatListEmptyRowItem.swift` (`ChatListSectionHeaderItem`) |
| Digest banner + modal | `FocusDigestController.swift` |
| Message layout (full-width) | `ChatRowItem.swift` |
| Media placeholders | `ChatFocusMediaPlaceholderItem.swift` |
| Compose area | `ChatInputView.swift`, `ChatInputActionsView.swift` |
| Theme lock | `Appearance.swift`, `AppDelegate.swift` |
| Feature flag | `InAppSettings` → `FocusProduct.isEnabled` |
